Method behavioural specifications:
- The integer array parameter `arr` must not be null.
- The length of the integer array parameter `arr` is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to 1000.
- All values in the integer array parameter `arr` are greater than 1 and are less than or equal to 10^9.
- The integer result is the number of binary trees that can be made using the integers in the array `arr`, modulo 10^9 + 7.